doctype html
| <
html(lang='en')
  head
    title Timestamp microservice
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css')
  body
    .container
      h1.header
        | API Basejump: Timestamp microservice
      blockquote
        | User stories:
        ul
          | 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string
          | contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
        ul
          | 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
        ul
          | 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
      h3 Example usage:
      code https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015
      br
      code https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/1450137600
      h3 Example output:
      code
        | {
        | &quot;unix&quot;: 1450137600,
        | &quot;natural&quot;: &quot;December 15, 2015&quot;
        | }
